â¨Must do road tripâ¨Share thisâ¨

The journey from NEPC Tea Estate to Sakthi Estate through Thalanar Estate, just before entering Valparai, is incredibly tranquil and unquestionably one of the must-do road trips in Tamil Nadu.

Your first destination will be Thalanar Snow Point, situated at a higher altitude, often shrouded in mist and strong winds, itâs said the weather changes every two hours.

Despite its seemingly simple structure, the experience is undeniably exhilarating.

Next, there are lots of waterfalls along the way, but be sure to stop at Thalanar Waterfalls and thereâs a high chance of spotting wildlife along the way.

To truly embrace the beauty of this place, I highly recommend a stay at Mistly Plantation @mistlybungalowsvalparai (Starting at 4000 INR per person, inclusive of dinner, breakfast, and various activities - 098435 44001).

Pro tips :

-> Best Season to visit post monsoon, please check once with the folks at Mistly plantation and plan accordingly.

-> Remember, thereâs a 100 INR fee per person at the check post, along with 100 INR per vehicle.

-> Also, note that the check post closes at 5 PM, so make sure to start your return by 4 PM.

-> While Sakthi Estate is considered the endpoint of the road, you can choose to turn back earlier if youâd like. We went a bit farther until Thalanar Waterfall and then turned around.

-> Also, thereâs a bus available from Kavarkal Junction for 8 INR, It takes you along the entire route and brings you back to the starting point.

A loud, hearty âaroooo!â Itâs a scene straight out of a comedy show!

Sure, this light bulb might not make it past a day in your house before getting swapped out for the right one. 

But think about the laughter, the teasing, and the love that fills the air because of this silly mistake. 

Those memories? 

Theyâre going to stick around a lot longer than any light bulb ever could.

So, letâs make a little more room for laughter in our lives. 

Letâs cherish the harmless mistakes, the mix-ups that leave us shaking our heads one minute and bursting into laughter the next. 

Because itâs these moments, these memories, that weave the rich tapestry of our lives together.

Remember, itâs not about being perfect. 

Itâs about enjoying the ride, missteps and all, and finding joy in the journey.

Take care,

- Mindset Mastery Crew

P.S. Next time something goes a bit sideways, instead of getting frustrated, try finding the humor in it. You might just end up with a great story to tell.

This video was taken on 8th March 2024 early morning at 3:30 am in Kumbalangi near Kochi, Kerala.  Initially, we didn't have any plans in Kochi because our collaboration got canceled, and couldn't travel to Bengaluru. But everything happens for good right! . We saw one reel about this and just booked it. It's kayaking in Kumbalangi backwaters. But at night. Kayak sessions are from 7 pm-3 am. You have to pre-book. The charges are from 800rs. I felt it was worth it!  They'll take you on a one-hour kayak and wherever you see, the water will be glowing when you kayak or splash the water. The interesting part is whenever the fish moves in water it glows due to bioluminescence. It's a magical experience. Shooting this might be tricky as we got very blurry videos because we only had phone cameras. 

We choose the Kayakify agency for this kayak. Overall it was a great experience for us. It also happens on the beach but it's a very rare phenomenon and might happen today and disappeare tomorrow. But here it's constant, it's there every day they said, and might be there till the end of March. So plan accordingly.

â¨One of India's most adventurous roads.â¨

Nestled in the scenic landscapes of Tamil Nadu, Kolli Hills is a small mountain range located in central Tamil Nadu, in the Namakkal district on the east coast of South India.

What sets Kolli Hills apart is its renowned hairpin bends - a whopping 70 of them. It offers an adrenaline-pumping experience for adventurers. 

These bends provide an adventurous driving experience amidst breathtaking scenery. While the road can be challenging with twists and turns, Some bends are pretty narrow, allowing only one vehicle to pass at a time.

The journey begins at Karavalli, at an altitude of 238 meters above sea level, and spans 20.4 km via 70 hairpin turns, concluding at 1,198 meters in Solakkadu. The elevation gain is 960 meters, and the average gradient is 4.70%.

It serves as an ideal weekend getaway for people from Bengaluru and Chennai.
